What are some applications of compressed encodings for binary trees?

Binary_tree
Encodings
Succinct encodings are the number of (internal) nodes; we don't even have to store its length. To show that no information is lost, we can convert the output back to the original tree as follows:

function DecodeSuccinct(bitstring structure, array data) {
  remove first bit from structure and put it in b;
  if b = 1 then
    create a new node n;
    remove the first element of data and put it in n.data;
    n.left = DecodeSuccinct(structure, data);
    n.right = DecodeSuccinct(structure, data);
    return n;
  else
    return nil;
}

More sophisticated succinct representations allow not only compact storage of trees but even useful operations on those trees directly while they're still in their succinct form.

